VHARISH BALM.S. Memorial Concert in Kochi featured Sreevalsan J. Menon's concert, which shone for its meticulous planning and astuteness in gauging the taste of the audience.He started his recital with `Ninnukori,' a varnam in Mohanam that was embellished withkalpana swaras.`Sreevaralakshmi,' the Dikshitar kriti in Sriraga, had  clear and precise sangatis.  `Seethapathe na manasuna' contrasted  with `Kanakashailaviharini,' a Shyama Shastri kriti in Punnagavarali.The concert invariably featured a few compositions that had been  popularised by M.S. One such composition was `Shambho Mahadeva,' one of Tyagaraja's Kovur Pancharatna kritis in Pantuvarali.Adding lustreEdapally Ajith on the violin  added lustre to Sreevalsan's Kedaragowla alaapana. Swati Tirunal's kriti `Jalajanabha' in misrachappu tala was rendered. The vocalist's neraval for `Karunalaya' was followed bykalpanaswaras, the best in the recital.Naanjil Arul ably tackled the tricky kalapramana on the mridangam.  Pramod accompanied on the ghatom.`Jagadodharana' in Kapi, which M.S. sang in her famed concert at the United Nations, was well sung by Sreevalsan. Swati Tirunal's Dhanashri tillana featured as the final piece.The concert was organised by Kerala Fine Arts Society and Bank Employees' Arts Movement.Bottom Template Starts
